{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6d469d42-45c7-4a6e-9f42-0e191dbe24fc","content":"No repo files to reference, so here's the guidance directly:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nAdd these packages to each test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\nAnd enable the new platform:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace VSTest@3 in your pipeline\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)\\TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | Built into each test app |\n| Task | `VSTest@3` | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (command: test) |\n| TRX | Automatic | `--logger \"trx\"` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publishing | Built-in | Separate `PublishTestResults@2` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n\n> **Tip:** Use `condition: always()` on the publish tasks so results are uploaded even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"58282978-4223-4e50-a373-28b765e82deb","outputTokens":665,"requestId":"A02C:2D289A:C33EAD:E3B200:69FE8614"},"id":"d274c13c-038c-4ce7-a4d0-20a698275811","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:56:00.668Z","parentId":"284d6451-a60f-4bd2-9b7e-2603a0bbce1e"}
